WEBVTT

00:00:00.760 --> 00:00:04.240
I bet all of you are familiar
with this view of the ocean,

00:00:05.280 --> 00:00:06.536
but the thing is,

00:00:06.560 --> 00:00:08.760
most of the ocean looks nothing like this.

00:00:09.480 --> 00:00:11.856
Below the sunlit surface waters,

00:00:11.880 --> 00:00:13.896
there's an otherworldly realm

00:00:13.920 --> 00:00:15.560
known as the twilight zone.

00:00:16.520 --> 00:00:19.776
At 200 to 1,000 meters below the surface,

00:00:19.800 --> 00:00:22.136
sunlight is barely a glimmer.

00:00:22.160 --> 00:00:25.256
Tiny particles swirl down
through the darkness

00:00:25.280 --> 00:00:27.816
while flashes of bioluminescence

00:00:27.840 --> 00:00:32.136
give us a clue that
these waters teem with life: